      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i noticed you listed things like suits, white shirts, and using utensils as the \"standard\" or \"baseline.\" if someone is coming from a culture where, say, traditional clothing or different ways of eating are the norm, how should they present themselves in these high-end settings to fit this \"universal\" standard without looking unprofessional? like, should they prioritize these western styles to be taken seriously?",
